title: P2_Day 1_LF 1
treatment_protocol_ch1: The mice were kept at 12:12 hr light: dark photoperiod with ad libitum access to food and water. Weaned mice at the age of 3-4 weeks were divided randomly into five groups- (each group contains 30 animals): first group was fed on normal diet (ND) with 10% of calories coming from fat, the second group was HFHSD fed group with increased sucrose and 60% of calories coming from fat (Research diets Inc.USA), and the third, fourth and fifth group of mice were fed on HFHSD with different doses of an ethano-botanical formulation, KAL-1 and we named them as HF5 (5µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD), HF20 (20µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD) and HF75 (75µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD). The daily weight of this aqueous formulation was 700 mg/ml. This dataset consists of gene expression changes in liver.
extract_protocol_ch1: The mice were periodically monitored over an eighteen week period. At the interval of every 3 weeks, five animals from each group were sacrificed and different tissues were extracted and frozen in liquid nitrogen prior to RNA extraction.
label_protocol_ch1: Agilent’s Quick-Amp labeling Kit (p/n5190-0444) was used following the manufacturer's protocol. T7 promoter based-linear amplification to generate labeled complementary RNA (One-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis)
hyb_protocol: Agilent’s In situ Hybridzation kit 5188-5242 was used following the manufacturer's protocol
scan_protocol: Slides were scanned immediately after washing on the Agilent DNA Microarray Scanner (G2505B) using one color scan setting for 4x44k array slides.
data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 9.1 (Agilent) using default parameters (protocol GE1-v1_91 and Grid: 012391_D_20060331) to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal. These intensities are used to calculate '75-percentile normalized data' and then fold changes using Agilent GeneSpring GX 11.0 software.

Weaned mice at the age of 3-4 weeks were divided randomly into five groups- (each group contains 30 animals): first group was fed on normal diet (ND) with 10% of calories coming from fat, the second group was HFHSD fed group with increased sucrose and 60% of calories coming from fat (Research diets Inc.USA), and the third, fourth and fifth group of mice were fed on HFHSD with different doses of an ethano-botanical formulation, KAL-1 and we named them as HF5 (5µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD), HF20 (20µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD) and HF75 (75µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD). The daily weight of this aqueous formulation was 700 mg/ml. This dataset consists of gene expression changes in liver.
extract_protocol_ch1: The mice were periodically monitored over an eighteen week period. At the interval of every 3 weeks, five animals from each group were sacrificed and different tissues were extracted and frozen in liquid nitrogen prior to RNA extraction.
label_protocol_ch1: Agilent’s Quick-Amp labeling Kit (p/n5190-0444) was used following the manufacturer's protocol. T7 promoter based-linear amplification to generate labeled complementary RNA (One-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis)
hyb_protocol: Agilent’s In situ Hybridzation kit 5188-5242 was used following the manufacturer's protocol
scan_protocol: Slides were scanned immediately after washing on the Agilent DNA Microarray Scanner (G2505B) using one color scan setting for 4x44k array slides.
data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 9.1 (Agilent) using default parameters (protocol GE1-v1_91 and Grid: 012391_D_20060331) to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal. These intensities are used to calculate '75-percentile normalized data' and then fold changes using Agilent GeneSpring GX 11.0 software.

Weaned mice at the age of 3-4 weeks were divided randomly into five groups- (each group contains 30 animals): first group was fed on normal diet (ND) with 10% of calories coming from fat, the second group was HFHSD fed group with increased sucrose and 60% of calories coming from fat (Research diets Inc.USA), and the third, fourth and fifth group of mice were fed on HFHSD with different doses of an ethano-botanical formulation, KAL-1 and we named them as HF5 (5µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD), HF20 (20µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD) and HF75 (75µg of KAL-1+ HFHSD). The daily weight of this aqueous formulation was 700 mg/ml. This dataset consists of gene expression changes in liver.
extract_protocol_ch1: The mice were periodically monitored over an eighteen week period. At the interval of every 3 weeks, five animals from each group were sacrificed and different tissues were extracted and frozen in liquid nitrogen prior to RNA extraction.
label_protocol_ch1: Agilent’s Quick-Amp labeling Kit (p/n5190-0444) was used following the manufacturer's protocol. T7 promoter based-linear amplification to generate labeled complementary RNA (One-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis)
hyb_protocol: Agilent’s In situ Hybridzation kit 5188-5242 was used following the manufacturer's protocol
scan_protocol: Slides were scanned immediately after washing on the Agilent DNA Microarray Scanner (G2505B) using one color scan setting for 4x44k array slides.
data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 9.1 (Agilent) using default parameters (protocol GE1-v1_91 and Grid: 012391_D_20060331) to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal. These intensities are used to calculate '75-percentile normalized data' and then fold changes using Agilent GeneSpring GX 11.0 software.
